# preparation
library("raster")
## Loading required package: sp
library("sp")
## raster elevation background
elevation <- getData("alt", country="PAK", mask=FALSE)
## Warning in showSRID(uprojargs, format = "PROJ", multiline = "NO", prefer_proj
## = prefer_proj): Discarded datum Unknown based on WGS84 ellipsoid in Proj4
## definition
plot(elevation) 

## vector map for Pakistan's boundary
pak <- getData('GADM', country='PAK', level=1)
plot(pak)

## setting extent
cropped_elevation <- crop(elevation, extent(pak))
plot(cropped_elevation)

## clip vector map using raster map
clipped_elevation <- mask(cropped_elevation, pak)
plot(clipped_elevation)
plot(pak, add=T)

## data frame of Pkistans participants location
participant_locations.csv <- read.csv("C:/Users/UNEEBA/Downloads/participant_locations.csv.csv")
locations <- participant_locations.csv
print(locations)
##         ..Name latitude Longitude                           Note
## 1 haseeb kamran 30.03863  70.63969 coordinates in decimal degrees
## 2 Uneeba Shahid 30.70584  70.64879 coordinates in decimal degrees
## 3 Mazhar Husain 30.52017  72.18643 coordinates in decimal degrees
## creating SpatialPointsDataFrame
spdf <- SpatialPointsDataFrame(cbind(locations$Longitude, locations$latitude), locations, proj4string=CRS("+init=EPSG:4326"))
plot(clipped_elevation)
plot(pak, add=T)
points(spdf, pch=16, cex=1, col="black")

## adding 3 largest cities
islamabad <- c(33.7215, 73.0433)
lahore <- c(31.582045, 74.329376)
karachi <- c(24.8666667, 67.05)
## creating its data frame
lat_ILK <- c(33.7215,31.582045,24.8666667)
long_ILK <- c(73.0433,74.329376,67.05)
df_latlong <- data.frame(lat_ILK, long_ILK)
rownames(df_latlong) <- c("islamabad", "lahore", "karachi")
print(df_latlong)
##            lat_ILK long_ILK
## islamabad 33.72150 73.04330
## lahore    31.58205 74.32938
## karachi   24.86667 67.05000
## now construct its SpatialPointDataFrames
spdf_cities <- SpatialPointsDataFrame(df_latlong, df_latlong,proj4string=CRS("+init=EPSG:4326"))
plot(clipped_elevation)
plot(pak, add=T)
points(spdf, pch=16, cex=1, col="black")
points(long_ILK,lat_ILK, pch=c(25, 22, 24), cex=1,col="black",bg=c("green","red","yellow"))

## now construct its SpatialPointDataFrames
marburg <- c(8.771994145830746, 50.801751971539)
